Cédric Patrice Thierry Villani (French: [se.dʁik pa.tʁis tjɛ.ʁi vi.la.ni]; born 5 October 1973) is a French mathematician working primarily on partial differential equations, Riemannian geometry and mathematical physics. He was awarded the Fields Medal in 2010 and is the director of Pierre and Marie Curie University's Institut Henri Poincaré.
Villani is also a politician. He sits in the National Assembly, the lower house of the French Parliament, representing Essonne's 5th constituency for En Marche!, the centrist political party of the French president Emmanuel Macron which currently holds the majority following the 2017 French legislative election. He was elected president of the French Parliamentary Office for the Evaluation of Scientific and Technological Choices in July 2017.
